[% META
        title = "Server Update Procedure - Step-by-Step Guide"
   description = "Comprehensive deployment procedures for Comserv production server updates"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "system"
   page_version = "1.02"
   last_updated = "2025-10-25"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'system/server_update_procedure.tt,v 1.02 2025/10/25 admin Exp admin - Consolidated Admin and System Versions' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Server Update Procedure - Step-by-Step Guide</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-10-25 | 
        Version: 1.02 | 
        Author: Admin | 
        Status: Production | 
        Note: Consolidated from admin/server_update_procedure
    </div>

    <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Important:</strong> This procedure should be followed carefully to ensure safe deployment of software updates to the production server. Always test changes thoroughly before deploying to production.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This document provides a comprehensive step-by-step process for updating software on the Comserv production server. The process ensures safe deployment with proper testing, backup, and rollback capabilities.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>SSH access to the production server</li>
                <li>Administrative privileges on the server</li>
                <li>Access to the development workstation</li>
                <li>Understanding of git workflow and branching</li>
                <li>Basic knowledge of Starman and Catalyst applications</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Step-by-Step Update Procedure</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 1: Login to the Starman Server</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Actions:</h4>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Connect to the production server via SSH</li>
                    <li>Navigate to the application directory: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">cd /opt/comserv</code></li>
                    <li>Verify current application status: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo systemctl status comserv-starman</code></li>
                    <li>Check current git branch: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">git branch</code></li>
                    <li>Note the current commit hash: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">git log --oneline -1</code></li>
                </ol>
                
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Expected Results:</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Starman service should be running and active</li>
                    <li>Current branch should be displayed (typically 'main')</li>
                    <li>Current commit hash recorded for rollback purposes</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting:</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>If Starman is not running: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo systemctl start comserv-starman</code></li>
                    <li>If git status shows uncommitted changes: Contact development team</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 2: Start the Development Server</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Actions:</h4>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Navigate to the Comserv directory: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">cd /opt/comserv/Comserv</code></li>
                    <li>Start development server on port 3001: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">CATALYST_DEBUG=1 perl script/comserv_server.pl -p 3001 -r &</code></li>
                    <li>Verify development server is running: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">curl -I http://localhost:3001</code></li>
                    <li>Note the process ID for later termination</li>
                </ol>
                
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Expected Results:</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Development server starts successfully on port 3001</li>
                    <li>HTTP response received from localhost:3001</li>
                    <li>Server runs in restart mode (-r flag ensures auto-restart on code changes)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting:</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>If port 3001 is in use: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo lsof -i :3001</code> and kill existing process</li>
                    <li>If dependencies missing: Run <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">cpanm --installdeps .</code></li>
                    <li>If database connection fails: Check <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">db_config.json</code> settings</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

<h3>Step 3: Transfer to Development Server in Restart Mode</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Open web browser to development server: <code>http://server-ip:3001</code></li>
    <li>Login with administrative credentials</li>
    <li>Verify all major functionality works on development server</li>
    <li>Keep development server running for testing new software</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Expected Results:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Development server accessible via web browser</li>
    <li>Login successful and admin functions available</li>
    <li>Current software version running on development port</li>
    <li>Server in restart mode will automatically reload after code changes</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>Benefits of Restart Mode:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Automatic restart when new software is pulled</li>
    <li>Immediate testing of changes without manual restart</li>
    <li>Isolation from production environment</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h3>Step 4: Backup the System Software</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Create backup directory with timestamp: <code>mkdir -p /opt/backups/comserv-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)</code></li>
    <li>Backup application code (excluding database): <code>rsync -av --exclude='logs/' --exclude='*.log' --exclude='db_config.json' /opt/comserv/ /opt/backups/comserv-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)/</code></li>
    <li>Create git tag for current state: <code>git tag backup-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)</code></li>
    <li>Record backup location and git commit hash</li>
    <li>Verify backup integrity: <code>ls -la /opt/backups/comserv-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)/</code></li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Expected Results:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete backup of application code created</li>
    <li>Git tag created for easy rollback reference</li>
    <li>Database and logs excluded from backup (not tracked files preserved)</li>
    <li>Backup location documented for potential rollback</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>What is NOT Backed Up:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Database content (handled separately)</li>
    <li>Log files (regenerated)</li>
    <li>Temporary files</li>
    <li>Configuration files with sensitive data</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h3>Step 5: Pull the New Software</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Ensure you're on the correct branch: <code>git checkout [branch-name]</code></li>
    <li>Pull latest changes: <code>git pull origin [branch-name]</code></li>
    <li>Check what files were updated: <code>git log --oneline -5</code></li>
    <li>Verify no merge conflicts occurred</li>
    <li>Update dependencies if needed: <code>cpanm --installdeps .</code></li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Expected Results:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>New software successfully pulled from repository</li>
    <li>No merge conflicts or errors</li>
    <li>Development server automatically restarts with new code</li>
    <li>Dependencies updated if cpanfile changed</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>Troubleshooting:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>If merge conflicts: Contact development team before proceeding</li>
    <li>If pull fails: Check network connectivity and repository access</li>
    <li>If dependencies fail: Check CPAN mirror availability</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h3>Step 6: Test the Software</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Verify development server restarted automatically</li>
    <li>Test application functionality on development server (port 3001)</li>
    <li>Check application logs for errors: <code>tail -f /opt/comserv/Comserv/logs/application.log</code></li>
    <li>Verify all dependencies are installed: <code>perl script/comserv_server.pl --help</code></li>
    <li>Test critical functionality matches workstation behavior</li>
    <li>If issues found: Make corrections on workstation, push to repository, and re-test</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Testing Checklist:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Application starts without errors</li>
    <li>Login functionality works</li>
    <li>Admin functions accessible</li>
    <li>Database connections successful</li>
    <li>No critical errors in logs</li>
    <li>New features work as expected</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>If Testing Fails:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Document the specific issues encountered</li>
    <li>Return to workstation to fix issues</li>
    <li>Push fixes to the repository</li>
    <li>Return to Step 5 to pull fixes and re-test</li>
    <li>Do NOT proceed to production until all tests pass</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<h3>Step 7: Merge to Main Branch (Workstation)</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions (Performed on Workstation):</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>When branch testing passes on server, return to workstation</li>
    <li>Switch to main branch: <code>git checkout main</code></li>
    <li>Merge the tested branch: <code>git merge [branch-name]</code></li>
    <li>Push merged changes to repository: <code>git push origin main</code></li>
    <li>Tag the release: <code>git tag release-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)</code></li>
    <li>Push tags: <code>git push origin --tags</code></li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Expected Results:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Branch successfully merged into main</li>
    <li>Changes pushed to remote repository</li>
    <li>Release tagged for future reference</li>
    <li>Main branch now contains tested changes</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>Best Practices:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Use descriptive commit messages</li>
    <li>Include issue/ticket numbers if applicable</li>
    <li>Document breaking changes in commit message</li>
    <li>Verify merge doesn't introduce conflicts</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h3>Step 8: Switch to Main and Test</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions (Back on Server):</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Switch to main branch: <code>git checkout main</code></li>
    <li>Pull latest main branch: <code>git pull origin main</code></li>
    <li>Verify development server restarts with main branch code</li>
    <li>Re-test application on development server</li>
    <li>Confirm all functionality works on main branch</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Expected Results:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Successfully switched to main branch</li>
    <li>Latest changes pulled from main</li>
    <li>Development server running main branch code</li>
    <li>All tests pass on main branch</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>Final Testing:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Verify no regressions introduced during merge</li>
    <li>Test both new and existing functionality</li>
    <li>Check performance hasn't degraded</li>
    <li>Confirm configuration files are compatible</li>
  </ul>
</div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 9: Docker Deployment Process (Authoritative Guide)</h3>
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase 1: Pre-Deployment (Workstation)</h4>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>Build latest image: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">docker compose build web-prod</code></li>
                    <li>Set deployment credentials: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">export SSHPASS='your_password'</code></li>
                </ol>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase 2: Production Preparation (Remote)</h4>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Check Disk Space:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">df -h /</code> and <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker system df -v</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Cleanup Old State:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker rm comserv2-web-prod-old 2>/dev/null</code> and <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker image prune -f</code></li>
                </ol>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase 3: Image Transfer & Backup</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Note:</strong> Image transfer via <code>docker save | docker load</code> only moves the <strong>image blueprint</strong>. It does <strong>not</strong> transfer running container instances, local volume data, or network configurations. These must be recreated or moved separately.</p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Transfer via SSH Pipe:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">docker save comserv2-web-prod | ssh ubuntu@192.168.1.126 "docker load"</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Backup Current Container:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker commit comserv2-web-prod comserv2-web-prod:backup-$(date +%s)</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Prepare for Switch:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker rename comserv2-web-prod comserv2-web-prod-old</code> and <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker stop comserv2-web-prod-old</code></li>
                </ol>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase 4: Execution (NFS vs Local Bind)</h4>
                <p>Test NFS reachability: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">showmount -e 192.168.1.175</code></p>
                <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0;">
                    <strong>Critical:</strong> Ensure stale volumes are removed to avoid conflicts.
                    <code style="display: block; margin-top: 5px;">sudo docker volume rm comserv2_comserv-workshop</code>
                </div>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>If NFS OK:</strong> Create volumes using project-prefixed names:
                        <code style="display: block; margin: 5px 0;">sudo docker volume create --driver local --opt type=nfs --opt o="addr=192.168.1.175,rw,noatime,nfsvers=3,soft" --opt device=":/mnt/data" comserv2_workshop_files_nfs</code>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Run Container:</strong> Use the updated volume names:
                        <code style="display: block; margin: 5px 0;">sudo docker run -d --name comserv2-web-prod -p 5000:3000 -v comserv2_comserv-logs:/opt/comserv/root/log -v comserv2_workshop_files_nfs:/data/nfs comserv2-web-prod:latest</code>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Phase 5: Verification & Cleanup</h4>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><strong>Health Check:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo docker inspect --format="{{.State.Health.Status}}" comserv2-web-prod</code></li>
                    <li><strong>Final Cleanup:</strong> Remove <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">comserv2-web-prod-old</code> and prune dangling images.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

<h3>Step 10: Implement Production Restart (Manual Method)</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Stop development server: <code>kill [development-server-pid]</code></li>
    <li>Restart Starman service: <code>sudo systemctl restart comserv-starman</code></li>
    <li>Verify Starman started successfully: <code>sudo systemctl status comserv-starman</code></li>
    <li>Check application logs: <code>tail -f /opt/comserv/Comserv/logs/application.log</code></li>
    <li>Test production application via web browser</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Expected Results:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Starman service restarts without errors</li>
    <li>Application accessible on production port (typically 5000)</li>
    <li>No errors in application logs</li>
    <li>All functionality works in production environment</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>Verification Steps:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Login to production application</li>
    <li>Test critical business functions</li>
    <li>Verify database connectivity</li>
    <li>Check external API integrations</li>
    <li>Monitor system resources</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<h3>Step 11: Final Testing and Monitoring</h3>
<div class="procedure-step">
  <h4>Actions:</h4>
  <ol>
    <li>Perform comprehensive testing of production application</li>
    <li>Monitor application logs for any errors</li>
    <li>Check system resources (CPU, memory, disk)</li>
    <li>Verify all integrations are working</li>
    <li>Document the successful deployment</li>
    <li>Clean up development server processes if no longer needed</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>Success Criteria:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Application responds normally to all requests</li>
    <li>No error messages in logs</li>
    <li>System performance within normal parameters</li>
    <li>All user-facing features functional</li>
    <li>Database operations completing successfully</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>Post-Deployment Tasks:</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Update deployment log with timestamp and version</li>
    <li>Notify stakeholders of successful deployment</li>
    <li>Schedule follow-up monitoring</li>
    <li>Clean up old backup files (keep last 5)</li>
  </ul>
</div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Rollback Procedure</h2>
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--danger-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Emergency Rollback:</strong> If critical issues are discovered after deployment, follow this immediate rollback procedure.</p>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Quick Rollback Steps:</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Stop Starman: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo systemctl stop comserv-starman</code></li>
                <li>Restore from backup: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">rsync -av /opt/backups/comserv-[timestamp]/ /opt/comserv/</code></li>
                <li>Reset git to backup tag: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">git checkout backup-[timestamp]</code></li>
                <li>Restart Starman: <code style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: 2px 4px; font-family: monospace;">sudo systemctl start comserv-starman</code></li>
                <li>Verify rollback successful</li>
                <li>Document issues for development team</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Automation Potential</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This manual process could be partially automated through the Comserv admin interface:</p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Proposed Automation Features:</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Development Server Management:</strong> Start/stop development server from admin panel</li>
                <li><strong>Git Integration:</strong> Branch selection and pull operations via web interface</li>
                <li><strong>Testing Dashboard:</strong> Automated testing checklist with pass/fail indicators</li>
                <li><strong>Deployment Workflow:</strong> Step-by-step guided process with confirmations</li>
                <li><strong>Rollback Interface:</strong> One-click rollback to previous stable version</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Current Limitations:</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Starman restart must be performed externally (cannot restart from within itself)</li>
                <li>Manual testing still required for complex functionality</li>
                <li>Network connectivity issues require manual intervention</li>
                <li>Database migrations may need manual oversight</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Best Practices</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Always test on development server before deploying to production</li>
                <li>Create backups before making any changes</li>
                <li>Document all deployment activities with timestamps</li>
                <li>Monitor application logs during and after deployment</li>
                <li>Have a rollback plan ready before starting deployment</li>
                <li>Coordinate with stakeholders for planned maintenance windows</li>
                <li>Keep deployment scripts and procedures up to date</li>
                <li>Test rollback procedures regularly in non-production environments</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting Common Issues</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Service Won't Start</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Check systemctl status and journalctl logs</li>
                <li>Verify configuration files are valid</li>
                <li>Check port availability</li>
                <li>Ensure all dependencies are installed</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Application Errors</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Check application logs in /opt/comserv/Comserv/logs/</li>
                <li>Verify database connectivity</li>
                <li>Check file permissions</li>
                <li>Ensure all required modules are installed</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Performance Issues</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Monitor system resources (CPU, memory, disk I/O)</li>
                <li>Check database query performance</li>
                <li>Review application logs for slow requests</li>
                <li>Consider restarting services if memory leaks suspected</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="info" style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Note:</strong> This procedure should be reviewed and updated regularly to reflect changes in the system architecture, deployment tools, and operational requirements.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>